Bank of Greece to drain 200bln drs via depo tender . Greece ' s central bank offered to drain up to 200 billion drachmas of 14 - day funds at 11 . 90 percent through a fixed interest rate tender on Wednesday , it said in a statement . Payment date is April 30 and maturity value date is May 14 , it said . " In case of oversubscription , bids will be satisfied pro rata , with a minimum allotment of 500 million drachmas . The Bank of Greece reserves the right to accept a higher total amount of deposits if this is viewed as enhancing the effectiveness of the auction , " it said . Bids should be submitted by fax between 1130 local ( 0830 GMT ) and 1230 ( 0930 GMT ) . - - Dimitris Kontogiannis , Athens Newsroom + 301 3311812 - 4 
